comments.body:
@jhoneill I haven't changed anything. The image is the color scheme right after install. I see the same behavior in the 5.x version of PowerShell as well.
For reference here is a screen cap from the colors tab from the Properties menu:
![image](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/4149865/145808762-163ba04c-405e-443b-85bd-8b38d8673c18.png)

@MAdrianMattocks  Compare your right most colour box to mine. Mine has R/G/B of  242/242/242, _something_ has changed yours.  If you change it to something contrasting, normality will return :-) 

I didn't think that Pwsh copied the console settings for PowerShell.exe; possibly it only does so if they've been changed.  
 PowerShell.exe has the background R/G/B of 1/36/86 you've got there.  You can try something which uses the console host but you don't normally run on its own (netsh, nslookup) and see if the defaults have been changed or if the settings came from PowerShell.
